### python Operators
## What are Python operators?
Python operators are used to perform computational operations on values and variables. They can be used to build both basic and complex algorithms. 
There are four commonly used operators in Python; 
- arithmetic, 
- assignment,
- comparison and 
- logical.

## Arithmetic operators
Arithmetic operators are used to performing mathematical computations such as addition, subtraction,
multiplication, and division.
Operators       Examples        Results
    +             2 + 2             4
    -             2 - 2             0
    *             2 * 5             10
    /             10/2              5
    %             10 % 4            2



## Assignment operators
Assignment operators are used to assign values to the variables. For the example below, let’s assume that x=20efor all examples.
Operators          Examples          Results
    =               x = 20              20
    +=              x += 10             30
    -=              x -= 10             10
    *=              x *= 10             200
    /=              x /= 10             2


## Comparison operators
Comparison operators are used to compare two values. It either returns True or False according to the condition.
Operators           Examples               Results
    ==              20 == 20                True
    !=              5 != 10                 True
    >               3 > 10                  False
    <               5 < 10                  True


## Logical operators
It is used to combine conditional statements. Logical operators will also return a True or False value.
Operators           Examples                  Results
    and             10<20 and 5>2               True
    or              10>20 or 5>2                True